<item>
            <title>[SPR-500] AbstractWizardController Doesn&apos;t Check Global Errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-500</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I first brought up this issue in the forums:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/viewtopic.php?t=413&amp;amp;start=0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/viewtopic.php?t=413&amp;amp;start=0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AbstractWizardController ignores GlobalErrors in validatePagesAndFinish.   It will redirect back to the form page if errors with the fields, but global errors don&apos;t redirect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I consider this a bug.  If not, what is the reason here?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
Seth&lt;/p&gt;</description>
